  <Docs>
    <summary>Describes the Vulkan YCbCr sampler conversion parameters used when creating a GPU-backed image from a YCbCr-encoded external texture.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`GRVkYcbcrConversionInfo` describes the parameters required to create a Vulkan YCbCr sampler conversion, which is used when sampling from a YCbCr-encoded image (such as a hardware video buffer) in a Skia GPU context.

The properties correspond directly to fields in `VkSamplerYcbcrConversionCreateInfo`. Use this struct with Skia's Vulkan backend when wrapping an external YCbCr texture.
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
